{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I want to talk about penguins today."},{"time":3000,"text":"But first, I want to start by saying that"},{"time":5000,"text":"we need a new operating system,"},{"time":7000,"text":"for the oceans and for the Earth."},{"time":10000,"text":"When I came to the Galapagos 40 years ago,"},{"time":12000,"text":"there were 3,000 people"},{"time":14000,"text":"that lived in the Galapagos."},{"time":17000,"text":"Now there are over 30,000."},{"time":19000,"text":"There were two Jeeps on Santa Cruz."},{"time":22000,"text":"Now, there are around a thousand trucks"},{"time":24000,"text":"and buses and cars there."},{"time":27000,"text":"So the fundamental problems that we face"},{"time":30000,"text":"are overconsumption and too many people."},{"time":33000,"text":"It's the same problems in the Galapagos,"},{"time":35000,"text":"except, obviously,"},{"time":37000,"text":"it's worse here, in some ways, than other places."},{"time":40000,"text":"Because we've only doubled the population of the Earth"},{"time":43000,"text":"since the 1960s -- a little more than doubled --"},{"time":46000,"text":"but we have 6.7 billion people in the world,"},{"time":49000,"text":"and we all like to consume."},{"time":51000,"text":"And one of the major problems that we have"},{"time":53000,"text":"is our operating system"},{"time":55000,"text":"is not giving us the proper feedback."},{"time":57000,"text":"We're not paying the true"},{"time":59000,"text":"environmental costs of our actions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"And when I came at age 22 to live on Fernandina,"},{"time":65000,"text":"let me just say, that I had never"},{"time":67000,"text":"camped before."},{"time":69000,"text":"I had never lived alone"},{"time":71000,"text":"for any period of time,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and I'd never slept with sea lions"},{"time":75000,"text":"snoring next to me all night."},{"time":78000,"text":"But moreover, I'd never lived on an uninhabited island."},{"time":81000,"text":"Punta Espinosa is where I lived for over a year,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and we call it uninhabited"},{"time":85000,"text":"because there are no people there."},{"time":87000,"text":"But it's alive with life;"},{"time":89000,"text":"it's hardly uninhabited."},{"time":92000,"text":"So a lot has happened in the last 40 years,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"and what I learned when I came to the Galapagos"},{"time":97000,"text":"is the importance of wild places, wild things,"},{"time":100000,"text":"certainly wildlife,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and the amazing qualities that penguins have."},{"time":105000,"text":"Penguins are real athletes:"},{"time":107000,"text":"They can swim 173 kilometers in a day."},{"time":110000,"text":"They can swim at the same speed day and night --"},{"time":113000,"text":"that's faster than any Olympic swimmer."},{"time":115000,"text":"I mean, they can do like seven kilometers an hour"},{"time":117000,"text":"and sustain it."},{"time":119000,"text":"But what is really amazing, because of this deepness here,"},{"time":122000,"text":"Emperor penguins can go down"},{"time":124000,"text":"more than 500 meters"},{"time":126000,"text":"and they can hold their breath for 23 minutes."},{"time":128000,"text":"Magellanic penguins, the ones that I work on,"},{"time":131000,"text":"they can dive to about 90 meters"},{"time":133000,"text":"and they can stay down for"},{"time":135000,"text":"about 4.6 minutes."},{"time":137000,"text":"Humans, without fins: 90 meters, 3.5 minutes."},{"time":140000,"text":"And I doubt anybody in this room"},{"time":142000,"text":"could really hold their breath for 3.5 minutes."},{"time":145000,"text":"You have to train to be able to do that."},{"time":147000,"text":"So penguins are amazing athletes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"The other thing is, I've never met anybody"},{"time":151000,"text":"that really doesn't say that they like penguins."},{"time":154000,"text":"They're comical, they walk upright,"},{"time":157000,"text":"and, of course, they're diligent."},{"time":159000,"text":"And, more importantly, they're well-dressed."},{"time":161000,"text":"So they have all the criteria"},{"time":163000,"text":"that people normally like."},{"time":165000,"text":"But scientifically, they're amazing because they're sentinels."},{"time":168000,"text":"They tell us about our world in a lot of different ways,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and particularly the ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"This is a picture of a Galapagos penguin"},{"time":175000,"text":"that's on the front of a little zodiac here in the Galapagos."},{"time":178000,"text":"And that's what I came to study."},{"time":180000,"text":"I thought I was going to study the social behavior of Galapagos penguins,"},{"time":183000,"text":"but you already know"},{"time":185000,"text":"penguins are rare."},{"time":187000,"text":"These are the rarest penguins in the world."},{"time":189000,"text":"Why I thought I was going to be able to do that, I don't know."},{"time":192000,"text":"But the population has changed"},{"time":194000,"text":"dramatically since I was first here."},{"time":196000,"text":"When I counted penguins for the first time"},{"time":198000,"text":"and tried to do a census,"},{"time":200000,"text":"we just counted all the individual beaks that we could"},{"time":202000,"text":"around all these islands."},{"time":205000,"text":"We counted around 2,000, so I don't know how many penguins there really are,"},{"time":208000,"text":"but I know I can count 2,000."},{"time":210000,"text":"If you go and do it now, the national parks"},{"time":213000,"text":"count about 500."},{"time":215000,"text":"So we have a quarter of the penguins"},{"time":217000,"text":"that we did 40 years ago."},{"time":219000,"text":"And this is true of most of our living systems."},{"time":222000,"text":"We have less than we had before,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and most of them are in fairly steep decline."},{"time":227000,"text":"And I want to just show you a little bit about why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"(Braying)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"That's a penguin braying"},{"time":236000,"text":"to tell you that"},{"time":238000,"text":"it's important to pay attention to penguins."},{"time":240000,"text":"Most important of all,"},{"time":242000,"text":"I didn't know what that was the first time I heard it."},{"time":245000,"text":"And you can imagine sleeping on Fernandina your first night there"},{"time":248000,"text":"and you hear this lonesome, plaintful call."},{"time":252000,"text":"I fell in love with penguins,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and it certainly has changed the rest of my life."},{"time":256000,"text":"What I found out I was studying"},{"time":258000,"text":"is really the difference in how the Galapagos changes,"},{"time":261000,"text":"the most extreme variation."},{"time":263000,"text":"You've heard about these El Ninos,"},{"time":266000,"text":"but this is the extreme that penguins all over the world"},{"time":268000,"text":"have to adapt to."},{"time":270000,"text":"This is a cold-water event"},{"time":272000,"text":"called La Nina."},{"time":274000,"text":"Where it's blue and it's green, it means the water is really cold."},{"time":277000,"text":"And so you can see this current coming up --"},{"time":279000,"text":"in this case, the Humboldt Current --"},{"time":281000,"text":"that comes all the way out to the Galapagos Islands,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and this deep undersea current, the Cromwell Current,"},{"time":287000,"text":"that upwells around the Galapagos."},{"time":289000,"text":"That brings all the nutrients:"},{"time":291000,"text":"When this is cold in the Galapagos,"},{"time":294000,"text":"it's rich, and there's plenty of food for everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"When we have extreme El Nino events,"},{"time":299000,"text":"you see all this red,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and you see no green"},{"time":303000,"text":"out here around the Galapagos."},{"time":305000,"text":"That means that there's no upwelling,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and there's basically no food."},{"time":310000,"text":"So it's a real desert"},{"time":312000,"text":"for not only for the penguins and the sea lions and the marine iguanas ..."},{"time":315000,"text":"things die when there's no food."},{"time":317000,"text":"But we didn't even know that that"},{"time":319000,"text":"affected the Galapagos when I went to study penguins."},{"time":322000,"text":"And you can imagine being on an island hoping you're going to see penguins,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and you're in the middle of an El Nino event"},{"time":327000,"text":"and there are no penguins."},{"time":329000,"text":"They're not breeding; they're not even around."},{"time":331000,"text":"I studied marine iguanas at that point."},{"time":334000,"text":"But this is a global phenomenon, we know that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"And if you look along the coast of Argentina, where I work now,"},{"time":339000,"text":"at a place called Punta Tombo --"},{"time":341000,"text":"the largest Magellanic penguin colony in the world"},{"time":343000,"text":"down here about 44 degrees south latitude --"},{"time":347000,"text":"you see that there's great variation here."},{"time":349000,"text":"Some years, the cold water"},{"time":351000,"text":"goes all the way up to Brazil,"},{"time":353000,"text":"and other years, in these La Nina years, it doesn't."},{"time":356000,"text":"So the oceans don't always act together; they act differently,"},{"time":359000,"text":"but that is the kind of variation"},{"time":361000,"text":"that penguins have to live with,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and it's not easy."},{"time":365000,"text":"So when I went to study the Magellanic penguins,"},{"time":367000,"text":"I didn't have any problems."},{"time":369000,"text":"There were plenty of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"This is a picture at Punta Tombo in February"},{"time":373000,"text":"showing all the penguins along the beach."},{"time":375000,"text":"I went there because the Japanese wanted to start harvesting them"},{"time":378000,"text":"and turning them into high fashion golf gloves,"},{"time":381000,"text":"protein and oil."},{"time":383000,"text":"Fortunately, nobody has harvested any penguins"},{"time":386000,"text":"and we're getting over 100,000 tourists a year to see them."},{"time":389000,"text":"But the population is declining"},{"time":392000,"text":"and it's declined fairly substantially, about 21 percent"},{"time":395000,"text":"since 1987, when I started these surveys,"},{"time":398000,"text":"in terms of number of active nests."},{"time":400000,"text":"Here, you can see where Punta Tombo is,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and they breed in incredibly dense colonies."},{"time":404000,"text":"We know this because of long-term science,"},{"time":407000,"text":"because we have long-term studies there."},{"time":409000,"text":"And science is important in informing decision makers,"},{"time":412000,"text":"and also in changing how we do"},{"time":414000,"text":"and knowing the direction of change that we're going in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"And so we have this penguin project. The Wildlife Conservation Society"},{"time":420000,"text":"has funded me along with a lot of individuals"},{"time":423000,"text":"over the last 27 years"},{"time":425000,"text":"to be able to produce these kinds of maps."},{"time":427000,"text":"And also, we know that it's not only"},{"time":429000,"text":"Galapagos penguins that are in trouble,"},{"time":431000,"text":"but Magellanics and many other species of penguins."},{"time":434000,"text":"And so we have started a global penguin society"},{"time":437000,"text":"to try to focus on the real plight of penguins."},{"time":440000,"text":"This is one of the plights of penguins: oil pollution."},{"time":443000,"text":"Penguins don't like oil"},{"time":445000,"text":"and they don't like to swim through oil."},{"time":447000,"text":"The nice thing is, if you look down here in Argentina,"},{"time":449000,"text":"there's no surface oil pollution from this composite map."},{"time":452000,"text":"But, in fact, when we went to Argentina,"},{"time":454000,"text":"penguins were often found"},{"time":456000,"text":"totally covered in oil."},{"time":459000,"text":"So they were just minding their own business."},{"time":461000,"text":"They ended up swimming through ballast water that had oil in it."},{"time":464000,"text":"Because when tankers carry oil"},{"time":466000,"text":"they have to have ballast at some point,"},{"time":468000,"text":"so when they're empty, they have the ballast water in there."},{"time":470000,"text":"When they come back, they actually dump"},{"time":472000,"text":"this oily ballast water into the ocean."},{"time":474000,"text":"Why do they do that? Because it's cheaper,"},{"time":476000,"text":"because they don't pay the real environmental costs."},{"time":479000,"text":"We usually don't, and we want to start"},{"time":481000,"text":"getting the accounting system right"},{"time":483000,"text":"so we can pay the real cost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485000,"text":"At first, the Argentine government said, \"No, there's no way."},{"time":487000,"text":"You can't find oiled penguins in Argentina."},{"time":489000,"text":"We have laws,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and we can't have illegal dumping; it's against the law.\""},{"time":494000,"text":"So we ended up spending nine years"},{"time":496000,"text":"convincing the government that there were lots of oiled penguins."},{"time":499000,"text":"In some years, like this year, we found"},{"time":501000,"text":"more than 80 percent"},{"time":503000,"text":"of the adult penguins dead on the beach"},{"time":505000,"text":"were covered in oil."},{"time":507000,"text":"These little blue dots are the fledglings --"},{"time":510000,"text":"we do this survey every March --"},{"time":512000,"text":"which means that they're only in the environment"},{"time":515000,"text":"from January until March,"},{"time":517000,"text":"so maybe three months at the most"},{"time":519000,"text":"that they could get covered in oil."},{"time":521000,"text":"And you can see, in some years over 60 percent"},{"time":523000,"text":"of the fledglings were oiled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"Eventually, the government listened"},{"time":527000,"text":"and, amazingly, they changed their laws."},{"time":530000,"text":"They moved the tanker lanes"},{"time":532000,"text":"40 kilometers farther off shore,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and people are not doing as much illegal dumping."},{"time":538000,"text":"So what we're seeing now"},{"time":540000,"text":"is very few penguins are oiled."},{"time":542000,"text":"Why are there even these penguins oiled?"},{"time":544000,"text":"Because we've solved the problem in Chubut province,"},{"time":547000,"text":"which is like a state in Argentina"},{"time":550000,"text":"where Punta Tombo is --"},{"time":552000,"text":"so that's about 1,000 kilometers of coastline --"},{"time":554000,"text":"but we haven't solved the problem"},{"time":556000,"text":"in northern Argentina, Uruguay and Brazil."},{"time":560000,"text":"So now I want to show you that penguins are affected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"I'm just going to talk about two things."},{"time":564000,"text":"This is climate change. Now this has really been a fun study"},{"time":567000,"text":"because I put satellite tags on the back"},{"time":569000,"text":"of these Magellanic penguins."},{"time":571000,"text":"Try to convince donors to give you a couple thousand dollars"},{"time":574000,"text":"to glue a satellite tag on the back of penguins."},{"time":577000,"text":"But we've been doing this now for more than a decade to learn where they go."},{"time":580000,"text":"We thought we needed a marine protected area"},{"time":582000,"text":"of about 30 kilometers,"},{"time":584000,"text":"and then we put a satellite tag on the back of a penguin."},{"time":586000,"text":"And what the penguins show us --"},{"time":588000,"text":"and these are all the little dots"},{"time":590000,"text":"from where the penguins' positions were"},{"time":592000,"text":"for penguins in incubation in 2003 --"},{"time":594000,"text":"and what you see is some of these individuals"},{"time":597000,"text":"are going 800 kilometers away from their nests."},{"time":600000,"text":"So that means as their mate"},{"time":602000,"text":"is sitting on the nest incubating the eggs,"},{"time":605000,"text":"the other one is out there foraging,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and the longer they have to stay gone,"},{"time":609000,"text":"the worse condition the mate is in when the mate comes back."},{"time":612000,"text":"And, of course, all of this then leads to a vicious cycle"},{"time":615000,"text":"and you can't raise a lot of chicks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"Here you see in 2003 --"},{"time":619000,"text":"these are all the dots of where the penguins are --"},{"time":621000,"text":"they were raising a little over"},{"time":623000,"text":"a half of a chick."},{"time":626000,"text":"Here, you can see in 2006,"},{"time":628000,"text":"they raised almost three quarters"},{"time":630000,"text":"of a chick per nest,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and you can see that they're closer to Punta Tombo;"},{"time":635000,"text":"they're not going as far away."},{"time":638000,"text":"This past year, in 2009,"},{"time":640000,"text":"you can see that they're now raising"},{"time":642000,"text":"about a fourth of a chick,"},{"time":644000,"text":"and some of these individuals are going"},{"time":646000,"text":"more than 900 kilometers away from their nests."},{"time":649000,"text":"So it's kind of like you having a job in Chicago,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and then you get transferred"},{"time":653000,"text":"to St. Louis,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and your mate is not happy about this"},{"time":657000,"text":"because you've got to pay airfare,"},{"time":659000,"text":"because you're gone longer."},{"time":661000,"text":"The same thing's true for penguins as well."},{"time":664000,"text":"And they're going about, on average now,"},{"time":666000,"text":"40 kilometers farther than they did a decade ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"We need to be able to get information out to the general public."},{"time":673000,"text":"And so we started a publication"},{"time":675000,"text":"with the Society for Conservation"},{"time":677000,"text":"that we think presents cutting-edge science"},{"time":679000,"text":"in a new, novel way,"},{"time":681000,"text":"because we have reporters that are good writers"},{"time":684000,"text":"that actually can distill the information"},{"time":686000,"text":"and make it accessible to the general public."},{"time":689000,"text":"So if you're interested in cutting-edge science"},{"time":691000,"text":"and smarter conservation,"},{"time":693000,"text":"you should join with our 11 partners --"},{"time":696000,"text":"some of them here in this room, like the Nature Conservancy --"},{"time":699000,"text":"and look at this magazine"},{"time":701000,"text":"because we need to get information out about conservation"},{"time":704000,"text":"to the general public."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"Lastly I want to say that"},{"time":708000,"text":"all of you, probably,"},{"time":710000,"text":"have had some relationship at some time in your life"},{"time":712000,"text":"with a dog, a cat, some sort of pet,"},{"time":715000,"text":"and you recognized that those are individuals."},{"time":717000,"text":"And some of you consider them almost part of your family."},{"time":720000,"text":"If you had a relationship with a penguin,"},{"time":723000,"text":"you'd see it in the same sort of way."},{"time":725000,"text":"They're amazing creatures"},{"time":727000,"text":"that really change how you view the world"},{"time":729000,"text":"because they're not that different from us:"},{"time":731000,"text":"They're trying to make a living,"},{"time":733000,"text":"they're trying to raise their offspring,"},{"time":735000,"text":"they're trying to get on and survive in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"This is Turbo the Penguin."},{"time":740000,"text":"Turbo's never been fed."},{"time":742000,"text":"He met us and got his name"},{"time":744000,"text":"because he started standing under"},{"time":746000,"text":"my diesel truck: a turbo truck,"},{"time":748000,"text":"so we named him Turbo."},{"time":750000,"text":"Turbo has taken to knocking on the door with his beak,"},{"time":752000,"text":"we let him in and he comes in here."},{"time":754000,"text":"And I just wanted to show you"},{"time":756000,"text":"what happened one day"},{"time":758000,"text":"when Turbo brought in a friend."},{"time":761000,"text":"So this is Turbo."},{"time":763000,"text":"He's coming up to one of my graduate students and flipper patting,"},{"time":766000,"text":"which he would do to a female penguin."},{"time":770000,"text":"And you can see, he's not trying to bite."},{"time":772000,"text":"This guy has never been in before"},{"time":774000,"text":"and he's trying to figure out, \"What is going on?"},{"time":776000,"text":"What is this guy doing?"},{"time":778000,"text":"This is really pretty weird.\""},{"time":780000,"text":"And you'll see soon"},{"time":782000,"text":"that my graduate student ..."},{"time":784000,"text":"and you see, Turbo's pretty intent"},{"time":786000,"text":"on his flipper patting."},{"time":788000,"text":"And now he's looking at the other guy,"},{"time":790000,"text":"saying, \"You are really weird.\""},{"time":792000,"text":"And now look at this: not friendly."},{"time":794000,"text":"So penguins really differ in their personalities"},{"time":797000,"text":"just like our dogs and our cats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800000,"text":"We're also trying to collect our information"},{"time":803000,"text":"and become more technologically literate."},{"time":806000,"text":"So we're trying to put that"},{"time":808000,"text":"in computers in the field."},{"time":810000,"text":"And penguins are always involved in helping us"},{"time":813000,"text":"or not helping us in one way or another."},{"time":816000,"text":"This is a radio frequency ID system."},{"time":819000,"text":"You put a little piece of rice in the foot of a penguin"},{"time":822000,"text":"that has a barcode, so it tells you who it is."},{"time":824000,"text":"It walks over the pad, and you know who it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826000,"text":"Okay, so here are a few penguins coming in."},{"time":829000,"text":"See, this one's coming back to its nest."},{"time":831000,"text":"They're all coming in at this time,"},{"time":833000,"text":"walking across there, just kind of leisurely coming in."},{"time":835000,"text":"Here's a female that's in a hurry. She's got food."},{"time":837000,"text":"She's really rushing back, because it's hot,"},{"time":840000,"text":"to try to feed her chicks."},{"time":842000,"text":"And then there's another fellow that will leisurely come by."},{"time":845000,"text":"Look how fat he is. He's walking back to feed his chicks."},{"time":848000,"text":"Then I realize that they're playing"},{"time":850000,"text":"king of the box."},{"time":853000,"text":"This is my box up here, and this is the system that works."},{"time":856000,"text":"You can see this penguin, he goes over, he looks at those wires,"},{"time":859000,"text":"does not like that wire."},{"time":862000,"text":"He unplugs the wire; we have no data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"So, they really are pretty amazing creatures."},{"time":872000,"text":"OK."},{"time":874000,"text":"Most important thing is:"},{"time":876000,"text":"Only you can change yourself,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and only you can change the world"},{"time":880000,"text":"and make it better, for people"},{"time":882000,"text":"as well as penguins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"So, thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}